fta for Best Television Serial in 2015 for The Lost Honour of Christopher Jefferies.\n\n", "biography_author": "Wikidata", "date_of_biography": "2023-08-01T15:49:19.832877+10:00", "external_links": [{"id": 4490, "uri": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kevin_Loader"}], "uuid": "c9e8511b-7414-4387-aa4e-3bb1926a479a", "source": {"name": "Vernon", "slug": "vernon"}, "source_identifier": "23296", "external_references": [{"id": 26910, "source": {"name": "Wikidata", "slug": "wikidata"}, "source_identifier": "Q28858652"}], "date_modified": "2023-09-13T12:30:51.070023+10:00"}, {"id": 36647, "name": "Bill Gunn", "roles_in_work": [{"id": 1999605, "title": "Ganja & Hess = Ganja and Hess", "work_id": 94579, "role": "director", "role_id": 938, "is_primary": true}], "also_known_as": "", "date_of_birth": "1934-07-15", "date_of_death": "1989-04-05", "genders": [{"id": 9, "name": "Male", "slug": "male"}], "languages": [{"id": 1, "name": "English", "slug": "english"}], "places_of_operation": [{"id": 1, "name": "United States of America", "slug": "united-states-of-america"}], "biography": "William Harrison Gunn (July 15, 1934 – April 5, 1989) was an American playwright, novelist, actor and film director. His 1973 cult classic horror film Ganja and Hess was chosen as one of ten best American films of the decade at the Cannes Film Festival, 1973. In The New Yorker, film critic Richard Brody described him as being \"a visionary filmmaker left on the sidelines of the most ostensibly liberated period of American filmmaking.\" Filmmaker Spike Lee had said that Gunn is \"one of the most under-appreciated filmmakers of his time.\"\nGunn's drama Johnnas won an Emmy Award in 1972.", "biography_author": "Wikidata", "date_of_biography": "2022-05-19T10:57:10.793740+10:00", "external_links": [{"id": 1729, "uri": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bill_Gunn_(writer)"}], "uuid": "d1d86f88-b6af-4a1c-acf4-6483a526f830", "source": {"name": "Vernon", "slug": "vernon"}, "source_identifier": "15966", "external_re